1
00:00:09,250 --> 00:00:11,208
[suspenseful music playing]

2
00:00:11,291 --> 00:00:12,833
[thunder cracking]

3
00:00:34,541 --> 00:00:39,083
Finally, my demonic power has returned.

4
00:00:39,583 --> 00:00:41,750
Once my liver is grown,

5
00:00:41,833 --> 00:00:46,541
nobody will ever again stand in my way.

6
00:00:47,333 --> 00:00:52,458
AGENT FROM ABOVE

7
00:00:53,166 --> 00:00:57,166
TURNING THE WHEEL

8
00:00:58,208 --> 00:01:00,208
[thunder cracks]

9
00:01:15,375 --> 00:01:16,208
Hey.

10
00:01:16,958 --> 00:01:18,083
What's wrong?

11
00:01:20,666 --> 00:01:23,833
Tien-chi said
he placed a demonic liver in me.

12
00:01:23,916 --> 00:01:25,708
It's no longer inside you.

13
00:01:27,333 --> 00:01:28,208
Then why…

14
00:01:29,416 --> 00:01:31,208
I gave you my liver.

15
00:01:31,291 --> 00:01:33,250
[sad music playing]

16
00:01:43,041 --> 00:01:44,583
It was my duty.

17
00:01:45,541 --> 00:01:46,458
I won't die.

18
00:01:48,041 --> 00:01:50,375
Consider it a staff benefit.

19
00:01:51,875 --> 00:01:54,791
[sniffles] The doctor,
he said my cancer's spread.

20
00:01:54,875 --> 00:01:57,333
I only have a few months left to live.

21
00:01:58,333 --> 00:02:00,625
You shouldn't waste energy on me.

22
00:02:01,916 --> 00:02:04,166
I should've died ten years ago.

23
00:02:04,791 --> 00:02:06,541
Each day I live is a bonus.

24
00:02:07,500 --> 00:02:08,916
I've lived my life.

25
00:02:11,083 --> 00:02:13,083
[sad music continues]

26
00:02:15,125 --> 00:02:16,041
I…

27
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:19,750
Will you win this time?

28
00:02:27,875 --> 00:02:29,125
After I do,

29
00:02:30,291 --> 00:02:31,958
we'll make a wish.

30
00:02:33,833 --> 00:02:35,791
[sobbing]

31
00:02:46,583 --> 00:02:48,250
Demon King has sourced his power.

32
00:02:48,333 --> 00:02:50,041
Take care of Yeh Tzu.

33
00:02:50,125 --> 00:02:51,958
- I must find him now.
- [Chang Mind] I'll come--

34
00:02:52,041 --> 00:02:54,583
What could you do?
How could you fight that thing?

35
00:02:54,666 --> 00:02:56,833
At least I'll feel good shooting him.

36
00:02:57,333 --> 00:03:00,625
You take care of my neighbors
and Yeh Tzu. I'm counting on you.

37
00:03:00,708 --> 00:03:02,541
[sad music continues]

38
00:03:09,708 --> 00:03:11,708
[grunts softly]

39
00:03:19,416 --> 00:03:20,666
DONGFENG MARKET

40
00:03:28,625 --> 00:03:29,708
[thunder cracking]

41
00:03:42,208 --> 00:03:43,041
[scoffs]

42
00:03:45,666 --> 00:03:46,708
[chuckles]

43
00:03:46,791 --> 00:03:49,333
You really are extraordinary.

44
00:03:49,833 --> 00:03:51,625
No liver,

45
00:03:52,125 --> 00:03:53,958
and yet you're still standing.

46
00:03:54,541 --> 00:03:56,958
Once you have my demonic liver,

47
00:03:57,041 --> 00:04:00,166
you'll never again
have to experience pain.

48
00:04:00,250 --> 00:04:03,875
At that time,
I'll no longer be considered human.

49
00:04:03,958 --> 00:04:08,375
If you do not spare the others,
you will not place the liver in me easily.

50
00:04:08,458 --> 00:04:10,083
[action music playing]

51
00:04:10,166 --> 00:04:11,875
[chuckling]

52
00:04:12,583 --> 00:04:16,708
I don't believe you ever planned
on letting me place…

53
00:04:16,791 --> 00:04:18,833
- [music stops]
- …the liver in you.

54
00:04:21,375 --> 00:04:23,083
[action music continues]

55
00:05:03,916 --> 00:05:05,125
[chuckling]

56
00:05:25,291 --> 00:05:28,333
Nine Dragons Divine Fire Barrier.

57
00:05:28,416 --> 00:05:31,166
This special treasure has returned to me.

58
00:05:31,791 --> 00:05:34,083
Spit it out right away.

59
00:05:34,583 --> 00:05:37,083
- [labored breathing] Fuck you.
- [chuckles]

60
00:05:37,166 --> 00:05:38,916
[action music continues]

61
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:47,958
[Han Chieh groaning]

62
00:05:55,875 --> 00:05:57,875
[cries]

63
00:06:03,833 --> 00:06:04,708
[choking]

64
00:06:19,833 --> 00:06:21,833
[music becomes meditative]

65
00:06:22,416 --> 00:06:24,208
[Han Chieh] <i>I know I don't have a choice.</i>

66
00:06:24,791 --> 00:06:26,166
<i>But I doubt I'll win.</i>

67
00:06:26,875 --> 00:06:28,375
[Crown Prince] <i>You'll work even harder.</i>

68
00:06:28,458 --> 00:06:31,708
You think I chose you just
because you're young and can fight?

69
00:06:32,708 --> 00:06:33,583
Then why did you?

70
00:06:34,083 --> 00:06:37,916
You can save all these souls.
It all depends if you're willing.

71
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:39,000
[music continues]

72
00:06:40,833 --> 00:06:43,208
[Han Chieh] <i>After I do, we'll make a wish.</i>

73
00:06:45,666 --> 00:06:47,250
[action music playing]

74
00:06:52,458 --> 00:06:53,875
How many have you hidden?

75
00:06:54,833 --> 00:06:56,500
[Han Chieh cries]

76
00:06:56,583 --> 00:06:58,291
[theme music playing]

77
00:07:12,125 --> 00:07:14,875
I just swallowed one.
There were four inside me.

78
00:07:14,958 --> 00:07:17,375
You can count how many dragons that is.

79
00:07:30,125 --> 00:07:34,000
If I can't win,
at least I'll destroy the liver. [grunts]

80
00:07:35,583 --> 00:07:37,291
[theme music continues]

81
00:08:04,166 --> 00:08:05,500
[music fades]

82
00:08:11,958 --> 00:08:13,958
[thunder cracking]

83
00:08:23,250 --> 00:08:25,541
[suspenseful music playing]

84
00:08:28,166 --> 00:08:30,500
You don't know what you're missing out on.

85
00:08:31,833 --> 00:08:36,041
You'd rather burn yourself to death
than be my agent.

86
00:08:37,750 --> 00:08:39,791
Let me ask you one last time.

87
00:08:40,958 --> 00:08:43,791
Are you ready to come work with me?

88
00:08:45,041 --> 00:08:50,208
Or do you want all the people here
to be buried alongside you?

89
00:08:50,291 --> 00:08:51,375
[ghosts squeal]

90
00:08:52,208 --> 00:08:54,041
Come on. Let's retreat.

91
00:08:54,125 --> 00:08:55,791
[action music playing]

92
00:08:56,458 --> 00:08:58,541
- Fuck!
- [screams] It's me.

93
00:08:58,625 --> 00:09:01,958
[screams] All our golden words
are destroyed. Quickly, they're coming.

94
00:09:02,041 --> 00:09:04,916
- It's going to be fine.
- [screams] They're all over the place.

95
00:09:05,000 --> 00:09:06,708
[music continues]

96
00:09:08,208 --> 00:09:09,500
Hang in there!

97
00:09:09,583 --> 00:09:11,583
[red ghost chuckles]

98
00:09:13,791 --> 00:09:15,916
[all clamoring]

99
00:09:16,000 --> 00:09:16,916
What's she doing?

100
00:09:19,708 --> 00:09:22,250
- She's gone weird.
- What's she doing, huh?

101
00:09:22,333 --> 00:09:23,791
- It's Yeh Tzu.
- Something's wrong.

102
00:09:24,375 --> 00:09:26,083
- [eerie music playing]
- [bird squawks]

103
00:09:31,083 --> 00:09:32,166
[chuckles]

104
00:09:33,916 --> 00:09:35,208
[screams]

105
00:09:35,291 --> 00:09:36,208
[Ms. Lo] Yeh Tzu!

106
00:09:37,250 --> 00:09:38,708
[action music playing]

107
00:09:38,791 --> 00:09:40,916
[A-Fu] Stop her! She's lifting the spell!

108
00:09:42,166 --> 00:09:44,375
Quickly, we need to get the golden powder.

109
00:09:50,041 --> 00:09:51,166
Move, move, move!

110
00:09:52,333 --> 00:09:53,708
[Yeh Tzu yelling]

111
00:09:58,375 --> 00:09:59,708
Go find Mr. Han!

112
00:10:03,375 --> 00:10:04,875
[music crescendos and stops]

113
00:10:09,541 --> 00:10:10,708
[eerie music playing]

114
00:10:19,375 --> 00:10:20,250
Let him go!

115
00:10:41,833 --> 00:10:46,791
So, it was you then, small boy,
who killed my evil spirits.

116
00:10:46,875 --> 00:10:48,375
[gun firing]

117
00:10:58,333 --> 00:11:00,625
[eerie music continues]

118
00:11:01,916 --> 00:11:03,375
Don't kid yourself.

119
00:11:13,458 --> 00:11:15,458
[groaning]

120
00:11:33,958 --> 00:11:35,291
[music turns curious]

121
00:11:44,625 --> 00:11:45,875
[music builds]

122
00:11:45,958 --> 00:11:47,958
[clangs loudly]

123
00:11:51,625 --> 00:11:53,625
[action music playing]

124
00:12:28,375 --> 00:12:30,625
The brat has actually showed up.

125
00:12:30,708 --> 00:12:31,958
[music fades]

126
00:12:32,041 --> 00:12:36,375
Haven't you always said it's beneath you
to possess someone's body?

127
00:12:36,916 --> 00:12:39,291
What changed? Are you panicking?

128
00:12:39,375 --> 00:12:40,875
Demon King,

129
00:12:41,500 --> 00:12:43,750
I have told you many times.

130
00:12:44,250 --> 00:12:46,708
Don't eat in such a rude way.

131
00:12:46,791 --> 00:12:50,000
I have to eat to gain
the strength to kill you!

132
00:12:53,666 --> 00:12:55,750
All these years, I've been planning

133
00:12:55,833 --> 00:12:58,166
how I'm gonna cut off
your legs and your arms.

134
00:12:58,250 --> 00:13:02,916
And then I'm gonna chop you
into tiny little pieces to vent my anger.

135
00:13:04,708 --> 00:13:06,500
- Okay then.
- [eerie music playing]

136
00:13:06,583 --> 00:13:09,125
We'll disregard that nagging heavenly rule

137
00:13:09,208 --> 00:13:11,250
and fight in our true forms.

138
00:13:11,791 --> 00:13:12,791
Not long now.

139
00:13:12,875 --> 00:13:15,875
Soon I'll eat up all the people
in the Human Realm,

140
00:13:15,958 --> 00:13:19,208
and then I'll become
more powerful than you all,

141
00:13:19,291 --> 00:13:23,125
and rule over all Three Realms.

142
00:13:26,000 --> 00:13:29,458
- You won't live that long.
- [action music intensifies]

143
00:14:19,708 --> 00:14:21,916
[action music continues]

144
00:14:38,041 --> 00:14:40,041
[theme music playing]

145
00:15:12,333 --> 00:15:14,333
[Crown Prince tutting]

146
00:15:15,583 --> 00:15:17,041
[Demon King] Damn this.

147
00:15:17,125 --> 00:15:19,708
Wu Tien-chi's body's too weak.

148
00:15:20,333 --> 00:15:22,708
I'd defeat you easily otherwise.

149
00:15:22,791 --> 00:15:25,541
If a human's body is unusable,

150
00:15:26,750 --> 00:15:28,375
then use your true form.

151
00:15:29,458 --> 00:15:32,583
[grunts] If I use my true form,

152
00:15:32,666 --> 00:15:35,041
I'd kill your agent from above.

153
00:15:35,125 --> 00:15:36,750
Could you bear that?

154
00:15:37,250 --> 00:15:40,125
Demon King, you're trying to provoke me

155
00:15:40,208 --> 00:15:42,333
to use my true form because you're losing.

156
00:15:42,416 --> 00:15:46,541
You want to make me violate
the heavenly rule, don't you?

157
00:15:47,125 --> 00:15:49,541
I've committed countless sins already.

158
00:15:50,125 --> 00:15:51,166
But I'm not like you.

159
00:15:51,791 --> 00:15:54,666
If you violate the heavenly rule,
you are in trouble.

160
00:15:55,250 --> 00:15:58,916
You're so badly behaved, there's no way
the higher-ups will spare you.

161
00:16:00,000 --> 00:16:01,041
Hey.

162
00:16:01,666 --> 00:16:05,333
Who do you think
channeled my spirit down here?

163
00:16:05,833 --> 00:16:07,500
- [dramatic music playing]
- Oh.

164
00:16:15,791 --> 00:16:18,916
The higher-ups think I'm rebellious.
That's just for show.

165
00:16:19,000 --> 00:16:21,791
- In private, they really love me.
- [grunts]

166
00:16:21,875 --> 00:16:24,541
You gods are all such hypocrites.

167
00:16:24,625 --> 00:16:27,625
Damn, you're actually playing
good cop, bad cop.

168
00:16:28,125 --> 00:16:31,375
The righteous path is a tougher journey
you see.

169
00:16:31,875 --> 00:16:35,875
The gods, they must destroy demons.

170
00:16:45,458 --> 00:16:47,833
[groaning]

171
00:16:51,500 --> 00:16:55,291
You little brat, even
your agent from above is extraordinary.

172
00:16:55,375 --> 00:16:57,166
In the Human Realm,

173
00:16:57,250 --> 00:17:00,666
there will always be more evil than good.

174
00:17:00,750 --> 00:17:02,416
Cut the crap!

175
00:17:05,333 --> 00:17:09,916
I will defeat you one day,
Third Crown Prince.

176
00:17:10,500 --> 00:17:14,041
You don't fight well,
but you know how to escape all right.

177
00:17:20,500 --> 00:17:22,500
[music fades]

178
00:17:23,083 --> 00:17:23,916
[groan]

179
00:17:26,375 --> 00:17:28,208
Crown Prince, you're merciful.

180
00:17:29,791 --> 00:17:31,791
[groans] Give me a chance.

181
00:17:31,875 --> 00:17:33,500
I'll be a better person.

182
00:17:34,083 --> 00:17:36,041
And sing your praises

183
00:17:36,625 --> 00:17:39,208
in the Human Realm.

184
00:17:41,375 --> 00:17:44,291
[chuckles] You've kept me busy lately.

185
00:17:44,875 --> 00:17:48,083
All the privileges
the Demon King promised you in hell,

186
00:17:48,166 --> 00:17:49,916
they're all gone now.

187
00:17:51,000 --> 00:17:52,125
<i>Finito</i>.

188
00:17:52,916 --> 00:17:55,375
[breathes nervously]

189
00:17:55,458 --> 00:17:59,083
You should know
what fate has in store for you.

190
00:17:59,166 --> 00:18:00,375
Do me a favor.

191
00:18:01,041 --> 00:18:01,875
Jump yourself.

192
00:18:01,958 --> 00:18:02,833
[Tien-chi grunts]

193
00:18:04,583 --> 00:18:06,583
[somber music playing]

194
00:18:07,916 --> 00:18:08,916
[Crown Prince] Hmm.

195
00:18:11,833 --> 00:18:14,583
I can't go to hell.
Please wait. I can't go to hell.

196
00:18:14,666 --> 00:18:17,375
Crown Prince, I beg you.
Please give me another chance.

197
00:18:17,458 --> 00:18:19,375
Give me one more chance, Crown Prince.

198
00:18:19,458 --> 00:18:22,208
I don't… I don't… I don't…
I don't want to go to hell.

199
00:18:22,291 --> 00:18:25,041
You've already had so many chances.

200
00:18:25,625 --> 00:18:28,375
But every time,
you choose the most evil path.

201
00:18:29,583 --> 00:18:31,000
I can't help you.

202
00:18:31,083 --> 00:18:33,333
You chose this yourself.

203
00:18:34,208 --> 00:18:36,208
- [sighs]
- [somber music continues]

204
00:18:36,708 --> 00:18:39,250
Han Chieh is a sinner.

205
00:18:39,333 --> 00:18:42,666
But he spent over ten years
paying for his sins,

206
00:18:42,750 --> 00:18:45,500
and would give his own life
to save others.

207
00:18:46,208 --> 00:18:47,416
And you?

208
00:18:51,083 --> 00:18:51,916
[groans]

209
00:18:52,000 --> 00:18:54,000
[music turns suspenseful]

210
00:19:14,166 --> 00:19:15,000
You're bad.

211
00:19:18,541 --> 00:19:22,041
Humans should deal with their own affairs.

212
00:19:23,916 --> 00:19:26,125
[somber music playing]

213
00:19:26,958 --> 00:19:28,416
[groans]

214
00:20:03,875 --> 00:20:05,416
So what if I wronged you?

215
00:20:05,500 --> 00:20:08,333
If you dare to mete out your own justice,

216
00:20:08,416 --> 00:20:11,166
you do deserve to be punished
down there, huh?

217
00:20:14,625 --> 00:20:15,666
[grunts]

218
00:20:17,125 --> 00:20:19,125
COMMAND

219
00:20:21,166 --> 00:20:23,125
The Black Command Token?

220
00:20:23,208 --> 00:20:25,958
I'm sorry.
He does things according to law.

221
00:20:26,666 --> 00:20:28,833
- [yells]
- [crying]

222
00:20:32,208 --> 00:20:35,083
[Crown Prince] <i>You've already had</i>
<i>so many chances.</i>

223
00:20:35,166 --> 00:20:36,541
<i>You chose this yourself.</i>

224
00:20:38,416 --> 00:20:40,791
[gasps]

225
00:20:40,875 --> 00:20:42,500
[dramatic music playing]

226
00:20:44,791 --> 00:20:45,833
You're Wu Meng-hsueh?

227
00:20:45,916 --> 00:20:46,750
UTTERLY EVIL

228
00:20:47,333 --> 00:20:49,458
- Who are you?
- I am Ox Head.

229
00:20:50,041 --> 00:20:51,958
Ox Head? Then this is…

230
00:20:52,041 --> 00:20:55,041
Quit your questions.
Can't you tell you're in hell?

231
00:20:56,041 --> 00:20:57,208
You'd better behave.

232
00:20:57,291 --> 00:21:00,875
Based on your record,
you will be here for hundreds of years.

233
00:21:00,958 --> 00:21:02,000
[engine revving]

234
00:21:02,083 --> 00:21:04,083
[groaning]

235
00:21:05,958 --> 00:21:07,958
[action music playing]

236
00:21:09,791 --> 00:21:11,541
[screams in the distance]

237
00:21:12,958 --> 00:21:13,791
[music fades]

238
00:21:17,500 --> 00:21:18,333
Han Chieh.

239
00:21:20,833 --> 00:21:21,708
Han?

240
00:21:23,041 --> 00:21:24,041
Han!

241
00:21:32,541 --> 00:21:33,875
I'm dead?

242
00:21:33,958 --> 00:21:35,958
[door opening]

243
00:21:37,541 --> 00:21:38,791
[Crown Prince] Hey, brat.

244
00:21:39,791 --> 00:21:41,208
Take a look at this.

245
00:21:47,333 --> 00:21:48,750
Where are my parents?

246
00:21:52,833 --> 00:21:54,833
[poignant music playing]

247
00:21:56,416 --> 00:21:57,750
Did they reincarnate?

248
00:21:59,708 --> 00:22:02,875
Before you even agreed to be an agent,

249
00:22:02,958 --> 00:22:05,541
they had already moved on,
and reincarnated.

250
00:22:07,083 --> 00:22:07,916
What?

251
00:22:09,333 --> 00:22:12,000
What you saw here were mirages.

252
00:22:12,083 --> 00:22:13,208
I tricked you.

253
00:22:15,541 --> 00:22:17,208
So they didn't suffer

254
00:22:18,041 --> 00:22:18,875
because of me?

255
00:22:21,666 --> 00:22:23,375
You're the one who's suffering.

256
00:22:26,166 --> 00:22:28,166
[poignant music playing]

257
00:22:39,291 --> 00:22:42,958
<i>Han Chieh, we're going to reincarnate now.</i>

258
00:22:43,041 --> 00:22:46,500
<i>When we enter oblivion,</i>
<i>we will forget you,</i>

259
00:22:46,583 --> 00:22:49,708
<i>so we can only</i>
<i>say goodbye to you in this way.</i>

260
00:22:49,791 --> 00:22:52,833
[mother] <i>All of this time we've been</i>
<i>so worried about you,</i>

261
00:22:52,916 --> 00:22:56,291
<i>and afraid that you blamed yourself,</i>

262
00:22:56,375 --> 00:22:58,333
<i>and have not lived well.</i>

263
00:22:59,125 --> 00:23:02,708
[dad] <i>My son, let bygones be bygones.</i>

264
00:23:03,666 --> 00:23:05,208
<i>I want you to know</i>

265
00:23:05,291 --> 00:23:08,708
<i>that even if I don't remember you</i>
<i>in my next life,</i>

266
00:23:08,791 --> 00:23:11,541
<i>you will always be the child that we love.</i>

267
00:23:12,041 --> 00:23:12,916
<i>Forever.</i>

268
00:23:13,875 --> 00:23:15,083
<i>We love you.</i>

269
00:23:15,166 --> 00:23:17,166
[poignant music continues]

270
00:23:18,041 --> 00:23:20,833
[videotape whirring]

271
00:23:24,666 --> 00:23:26,250
[sighs heavily]

272
00:23:40,083 --> 00:23:42,125
[calm music playing]

273
00:23:42,208 --> 00:23:45,541
Your parents may not
have taught you everything,

274
00:23:45,625 --> 00:23:48,375
but that doesn't warrant
punishment in hell.

275
00:23:50,708 --> 00:23:54,166
So that's why I let them reincarnate.

276
00:23:55,166 --> 00:23:56,500
But as you know,

277
00:23:56,583 --> 00:24:00,208
if you want to reincarnate,
there's a price to pay, huh?

278
00:24:02,000 --> 00:24:03,458
That's how it is.

279
00:24:03,541 --> 00:24:09,125
I'll treat the work you've done for me
as a down payment on your first debt.

280
00:24:09,208 --> 00:24:10,750
Congratulations.

281
00:24:10,833 --> 00:24:12,125
The first debt?

282
00:24:12,791 --> 00:24:14,291
How many do I have?

283
00:24:18,916 --> 00:24:21,250
Life and death are predestined.

284
00:24:21,333 --> 00:24:23,291
When it comes to this girl's illness,

285
00:24:23,375 --> 00:24:26,625
even I can't prolong her life.

286
00:24:29,416 --> 00:24:30,375
I can't save her.

287
00:24:31,791 --> 00:24:32,875
Yet you saved me?

288
00:24:33,958 --> 00:24:35,791
I seized an opportunity.

289
00:24:35,875 --> 00:24:37,291
You were fated to die.

290
00:24:37,916 --> 00:24:40,916
You were special,
destined to do good deeds.

291
00:24:41,000 --> 00:24:43,000
[poignant music continues]

292
00:24:46,708 --> 00:24:47,625
However…

293
00:24:50,000 --> 00:24:52,291
I can give her a liver

294
00:24:53,875 --> 00:24:57,583
since she suffers due to the Demon King.

295
00:25:14,916 --> 00:25:18,708
Giving her this can relieve her pain,

296
00:25:18,791 --> 00:25:20,500
but it can't prolong her life.

297
00:25:21,083 --> 00:25:24,541
How long she will live
depends on her own fate.

298
00:25:25,208 --> 00:25:28,125
So if she gets this, she may not live?

299
00:25:29,625 --> 00:25:30,833
Maybe not.

300
00:25:30,916 --> 00:25:32,083
There's a price.

301
00:25:35,208 --> 00:25:37,541
CONTRACT: THIRD CROWN PRINCE'S AGENT
IN THE HUMAN REALM

302
00:25:38,291 --> 00:25:39,125
What's this?

303
00:25:39,208 --> 00:25:42,666
- [intriguing music playing]
- A contract for you to renew.

304
00:25:42,750 --> 00:25:45,708
I told you, you owe me more than one debt.

305
00:25:45,791 --> 00:25:47,666
I, HAN CHIEH, AM WILLING
TO RENEW THE CONTRACT

306
00:25:47,750 --> 00:25:50,750
AND BE THE THIRD CROWN PRINCE'S AGENT
IN THE HUMAN REALM

307
00:25:50,833 --> 00:25:52,583
[theme music playing]

308
00:25:52,666 --> 00:25:56,666
This is part of the contract.

309
00:26:00,916 --> 00:26:02,583
[music intensifies]

310
00:26:07,958 --> 00:26:09,083
I'll sign.

311
00:26:12,041 --> 00:26:13,250
HAN CHIEH

312
00:26:16,625 --> 00:26:18,875
THIRD CROWN PRINCE'S AGENT
IN THE HUMAN REALM

313
00:26:43,083 --> 00:26:44,333
[Crown Prince] Remember.

314
00:26:44,416 --> 00:26:46,291
Use incense and smoke it daily.

315
00:26:46,375 --> 00:26:47,666
And after 49 days,

316
00:26:48,541 --> 00:26:50,416
you'll find the truth.

317
00:26:50,500 --> 00:26:52,333
- Okay?
- [music fades]

318
00:26:54,750 --> 00:26:56,125
And in the meantime,

319
00:26:56,708 --> 00:27:00,458
just enjoy a well-deserved vacation, huh?

320
00:27:00,541 --> 00:27:02,708
Fuck. Why am I so nice?

321
00:27:03,666 --> 00:27:04,750
Crown Prince.

322
00:27:08,333 --> 00:27:09,791
I don't understand.

323
00:27:11,708 --> 00:27:12,958
Why was it me?

324
00:27:16,500 --> 00:27:20,125
There are so many people
who are better than me.

325
00:27:22,166 --> 00:27:24,208
Why do I get a second chance?

326
00:27:24,291 --> 00:27:26,291
[poignant music playing]

327
00:27:28,041 --> 00:27:30,250
FENGYUAN TEMPLE,
MARSHAL OF THE CENTRAL ALTAR

328
00:27:30,333 --> 00:27:34,625
[Crown Prince] <i>Maybe you didn't know,</i>
<i>but I was always by your side.</i>

329
00:27:37,416 --> 00:27:40,125
<i>When you were little, you loved your bike.</i>

330
00:27:40,208 --> 00:27:42,791
<i>I watched you ride around every day.</i>

331
00:27:45,875 --> 00:27:48,375
- [dad] Han Chieh, don't run around.
- [mom] Listen to your father.

332
00:27:48,458 --> 00:27:51,125
The first time you talked back
to your parents was

333
00:27:51,208 --> 00:27:53,666
because you wanted
to adopt a homeless cat.

334
00:27:53,750 --> 00:27:55,958
- It's mine!
- Don't be so angry.

335
00:27:56,791 --> 00:27:58,750
<i>You eventually got your way.</i>

336
00:27:59,250 --> 00:28:00,125
Loser!

337
00:28:01,083 --> 00:28:05,791
<i>The first time you got into a fight</i>
<i>was to protect a bullied classmate.</i>

338
00:28:05,875 --> 00:28:07,583
FENGYUAN TEMPLE

339
00:28:07,666 --> 00:28:10,375
[clamoring in the background]

340
00:28:14,916 --> 00:28:16,916
- [poignant music continues]
- [sobbing]

341
00:28:17,416 --> 00:28:19,958
<i>On the worst day of your life,</i>

342
00:28:21,000 --> 00:28:22,208
<i>I was there too.</i>

343
00:28:25,250 --> 00:28:27,250
[continues sobbing]

344
00:28:28,583 --> 00:28:30,041
<i>I watched you grow up.</i>

345
00:28:30,750 --> 00:28:32,416
So I think I know you well.

346
00:28:33,708 --> 00:28:36,541
When you were led astray
and made mistakes,

347
00:28:36,625 --> 00:28:38,875
you accepted the consequences.

348
00:28:40,000 --> 00:28:43,541
If I didn't give you this chance,
then who would I?

349
00:28:44,708 --> 00:28:45,916
[chuckles softly]

350
00:28:46,000 --> 00:28:48,750
I'm watching you, so work hard.

351
00:28:50,875 --> 00:28:52,875
[poignant music builds]

352
00:29:05,583 --> 00:29:08,041
QIANKUN HOOP

353
00:29:09,500 --> 00:29:11,041
FIRE-TIPPED SPEAR

354
00:29:12,125 --> 00:29:14,041
GOLDEN BRICK

355
00:29:14,625 --> 00:29:17,041
RED ARMILLARY SASH

356
00:29:17,125 --> 00:29:20,041
LEOPARD-SKIN POUCH

357
00:29:21,208 --> 00:29:23,000
WIND FIRE WHEELS

358
00:29:24,208 --> 00:29:26,708
NINE DRAGONS DIVINE FIRE BARRIER

359
00:29:54,500 --> 00:29:56,333
- [music fades]
- [bird chirps softly]

360
00:29:56,416 --> 00:30:00,625
DONGFENG MARKET

361
00:30:10,916 --> 00:30:13,000
Mr. Han, here's the lighter.

362
00:30:33,833 --> 00:30:34,666
[Chang Min] Mmm.

363
00:30:46,708 --> 00:30:48,000
Do you regret it?

364
00:30:48,833 --> 00:30:49,708
Regret what?

365
00:30:50,291 --> 00:30:51,541
Renewing your contract.

366
00:30:52,666 --> 00:30:53,958
Yeh Tzu.

367
00:30:57,958 --> 00:30:59,958
[sentimental music playing]

368
00:31:01,875 --> 00:31:02,958
I don't.

369
00:31:04,500 --> 00:31:05,750
It was a good deal.

370
00:31:07,125 --> 00:31:08,666
She was happy,

371
00:31:10,250 --> 00:31:11,458
before she died.

372
00:31:29,166 --> 00:31:30,750
[cell phone chimes]

373
00:31:39,250 --> 00:31:42,125
SENDER: LEAFY
SENT TO: HAN CHIEH

374
00:31:45,083 --> 00:31:47,500
[Yeh Tzu] <i>Mr. Han,</i>
<i>I hope you're doing well.</i>

375
00:31:48,875 --> 00:31:52,166
<i>When you're reading this,</i>
<i>I'll already be gone.</i>

376
00:31:53,083 --> 00:31:56,125
<i>It's my last time I'll be sending</i>
<i>a message to anyone,</i>

377
00:31:56,208 --> 00:31:59,416
<i>so please be patient</i>
<i>and read through this to the end.</i>

378
00:32:00,625 --> 00:32:02,166
[sentimental music continues]

379
00:32:02,250 --> 00:32:06,541
<i>After I fell ill,</i>
<i>I realized I should do something,</i>

380
00:32:06,625 --> 00:32:08,666
<i>so my life was not a waste.</i>

381
00:32:10,083 --> 00:32:14,166
<i>I was confused the first time</i>
<i>I went to Dongfeng Market,</i>

382
00:32:14,750 --> 00:32:18,041
<i>and met you, and all the other folk there.</i>

383
00:32:18,125 --> 00:32:19,083
<i>It made me realize</i>

384
00:32:19,166 --> 00:32:22,041
<i>there's a different kind</i>
<i>of existence after you die,</i>

385
00:32:22,125 --> 00:32:23,708
<i>That's why I'm not afraid anymore.</i>

386
00:32:23,791 --> 00:32:26,083
You made a friend? Won't you introduce me?

387
00:32:26,666 --> 00:32:31,250
<i>In the last moments of my life,</i>
<i>I received so much love.</i>

388
00:32:31,333 --> 00:32:34,041
<i>It was the happiest time of my life.</i>

389
00:32:34,125 --> 00:32:35,375
GET WELL SOON!

390
00:32:35,458 --> 00:32:37,041
LEAFY, GET WELL SOON!

391
00:32:37,125 --> 00:32:38,500
LET'S TRAVEL ABROAD AGAIN!

392
00:32:38,583 --> 00:32:42,458
<i>There are many things</i>
<i>that I didn't have the time to do.</i>

393
00:32:42,958 --> 00:32:45,958
<i>But maybe there's still</i>
<i>a chance to do things.</i>

394
00:32:46,458 --> 00:32:50,333
<i>You can fill my spot playing video games</i>
<i>with the old man.</i>

395
00:32:50,416 --> 00:32:52,875
<i>And for heaven's sake,</i>
<i>look after yourself.</i>

396
00:32:52,958 --> 00:32:54,041
[music continues]

397
00:32:54,125 --> 00:32:57,750
<i>Lastly, I have a favor to ask of you.</i>

398
00:32:59,333 --> 00:33:02,333
<i>I hope that</i>
<i>you can love this world for me,</i>

399
00:33:02,958 --> 00:33:04,416
<i>whether it's messy,</i>

400
00:33:04,500 --> 00:33:07,666
<i>and even the gods</i>
<i>can't do anything about it.</i>

401
00:33:08,958 --> 00:33:12,583
<i>I think the ones who might really</i>
<i>change the world for the better</i>

402
00:33:13,875 --> 00:33:16,166
<i>are just ordinary people like us.</i>

403
00:33:26,541 --> 00:33:28,166
My son's amazing.

404
00:33:28,666 --> 00:33:34,791
LATE FATHER CHANG HO-CHENG,
WORSHIPED BY FILIAL SON CHANG MIN

405
00:33:34,875 --> 00:33:37,250
- [old man laughs] You draw now.
- White Dragon? Wow.

406
00:33:37,333 --> 00:33:39,000
Time to eat. Come get some food.

407
00:33:39,083 --> 00:33:42,000
Go. Oh, good job.

408
00:33:42,083 --> 00:33:43,833
Oh, you're good at this.

409
00:33:44,333 --> 00:33:46,541
[sentimental music continues]

410
00:33:46,625 --> 00:33:49,916
[man and woman praying indistinctly]

411
00:34:04,458 --> 00:34:05,458
[Yeh Tzu] <i>Mr. Han.</i>

412
00:34:06,333 --> 00:34:09,791
<i>If I wish for world peace,</i>
<i>can you wish it too?</i>

413
00:34:21,333 --> 00:34:24,333
WORLD PEACE

414
00:34:28,500 --> 00:34:29,791
<i>Make a wish.</i>

415
00:34:35,916 --> 00:34:38,083
MARSHAL OF THE CENTRAL ALTAR

416
00:34:39,208 --> 00:34:42,666
<i>The old man told me</i>
<i>magic can't defeat spiritual power,</i>

417
00:34:42,750 --> 00:34:45,125
<i>spiritual power can't defeat karma,</i>

418
00:34:45,208 --> 00:34:47,291
<i>and karma can't defeat a wish.</i>

419
00:34:49,666 --> 00:34:54,458
<i>So a person with a wish</i>
<i>is strongest of all.</i>

420
00:34:54,541 --> 00:34:56,541
[sentimental music continues]

421
00:35:02,833 --> 00:35:09,791
WORLD PEACE
MARSHAL OF THE CENTRAL ALTAR

422
00:35:20,125 --> 00:35:23,666
DONGFENG MARKET

423
00:35:23,750 --> 00:35:25,000
[bird chirps]

424
00:35:29,833 --> 00:35:31,000
[footsteps approaching]

425
00:35:32,875 --> 00:35:34,875
[eerie music playing]

426
00:35:51,916 --> 00:35:53,916
[doorbell ringing]

427
00:35:59,541 --> 00:36:00,583
Who are you?

428
00:36:01,166 --> 00:36:02,208
Hi.

429
00:36:08,958 --> 00:36:09,958
You brought a ghost?

430
00:36:10,041 --> 00:36:11,625
Wow, it's true.

431
00:36:11,708 --> 00:36:13,166
You can really see it.

432
00:36:13,250 --> 00:36:14,666
Let me introduce myself.

433
00:36:15,250 --> 00:36:16,125
My name's Li.

434
00:36:16,208 --> 00:36:17,375
- I've come--
- Wait on.

435
00:36:18,541 --> 00:36:20,333
- Your name is Li?
- Yes.

436
00:36:22,333 --> 00:36:23,875
TO SEIZE INHERITANCE

437
00:36:23,958 --> 00:36:27,375
MR. LI HIRED A GHOST TO KILL ELDERS,
WANTS TO AVOID PUNISHMENT

438
00:36:27,458 --> 00:36:28,875
BEAT HIM UP

439
00:36:30,375 --> 00:36:32,750
- [action music playing]
- Wait!

440
00:36:33,625 --> 00:36:35,541
I came on some business.

441
00:36:36,125 --> 00:36:39,000
Shouldn't you check with your boss?
[chuckles]

442
00:36:40,083 --> 00:36:41,041
Woah!

443
00:36:42,500 --> 00:36:44,416
I don't need to ask instructions.

444
00:36:44,500 --> 00:36:46,041
His instructions never change.

445
00:36:50,291 --> 00:36:52,291
[action music continues]

446
00:36:58,208 --> 00:36:59,708
Kill demons.

447
00:36:59,791 --> 00:37:01,791
[theme music playing]

448
00:37:06,916 --> 00:37:10,500
AGENT FROM ABOVE

449
00:37:19,333 --> 00:37:21,416
[music fades]

450
00:37:25,708 --> 00:37:28,666
[man] Money makes the world go round.

451
00:37:29,166 --> 00:37:32,875
Hell is even darker than the human world.

452
00:37:32,958 --> 00:37:36,166
Some old scores can be settled
while you're alive.

453
00:37:36,250 --> 00:37:38,250
[suspenseful music playing]

454
00:37:39,750 --> 00:37:41,833
But with this Talisman…

455
00:37:44,208 --> 00:37:46,000
after death,

456
00:37:47,125 --> 00:37:50,500
you can change everything
any way you want.

457
00:37:50,583 --> 00:37:51,666
HELL TALISMAN

458
00:37:53,375 --> 00:37:55,375
[suspenseful music intensifies]

459
00:38:00,083 --> 00:38:01,541
[music builds]

460
00:38:08,541 --> 00:38:09,916
[yells]

461
00:38:15,625 --> 00:38:16,875
[yells]

462
00:38:37,416 --> 00:38:39,083
[music builds]

463
00:38:39,875 --> 00:38:41,625
I want you

464
00:38:42,375 --> 00:38:44,000
to kill someone.

465
00:38:47,166 --> 00:38:48,000
[growls]

466
00:38:53,250 --> 00:38:55,250
[music fades]

467
00:38:56,000 --> 00:38:58,000
[theme music playing]

468
00:39:56,000 --> 00:39:58,000
[music continues]

469
00:40:54,375 --> 00:40:56,375
[music continues]

470
00:41:54,375 --> 00:41:56,375
[music continues]

471
00:42:54,375 --> 00:42:56,375
[music continues]

472
00:43:51,750 --> 00:43:53,750
[music ends]
